To avoid having multiple returns, I'd suggest setting up a variable, filling if it necessary, and then returning it, e.g.:
let fileList = [];
if (xpiName){ fileList = [{ ... }]; }
return fileList;

The linter will occasionally flag unreachable code when there are multiple returns in a function, so I try to take this approach when possible.

body:
To avoid having multiple `return`s, I'd suggest setting up a variable, filling if it necessary, and then returning it, e.g.:

```
let fileList = [];
if (xpiName){ fileList = [{ ... }]; }
return fileList;
```

The linter will occasionally flag `unreachable code` when there are multiple returns in a function, so I try to take this approach when possible.
